description:
&lt;p&gt;We are delighted to be able to offer an opportunity for a highly motivated individual to join our Fire Advisor Team.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;The Fire Advisor team are there to provide expert fire safety and evacuation advice to the Trust to ensure compliance with The Regulatory Reform (Fire Safety) Order 2005.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;The role is working closely within the Estates Department and all Operational departments across the Trust. Within this role you will report directly to the Trust Lead Fire Advisor.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;Duties include;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;ul&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Providing specialist advice to internal and external stakeholders&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Carrying out and assessing fire risk assessments&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Ensuring the inspection and maintenance of all fire safety systems&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Ensuring compliance with current legislation across the Trust&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Assisting with Evacuation Exercises&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;/ul&gt;
&lt;p&gt;You will be expected to have knowledge of fire safety principles and current legislation, including health and safety. You will be responsible for implementing and developing mandatory fire safety training (including staff induction). You will also contribute to project designs and training development.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;As the direct liaison for internal and external stakeholders, excellent communication skills will be required.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;Please refer to the Job Description and Person Specification for all essential and desirable criteria required for the role.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;Full Time 37 Hours 30 Minutes/Week&lt;/p&gt;
